This paper deals with the security analysis of cryptographic protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of mathematical tools and concepts, such as witness functions and the little theorem, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the formal analysis of a protocol, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
